                        <bindingDesc>
                            <binding contemporary="true">
                                <p>Medieval binding. Blue leather over wooden boards. 4 double raised bands and endbands. <locus from="LCO" to="LCO" scheme="other"/>: 2 hooked clasp metal catchplates engraved with a flower and finishing in a butterfly shape; <locus from="LCO" to="LCO" scheme="other"/> and <locus from="RCO" to="RCO" scheme="other"/>: bronze edge strips engraved with small stripes at the edges; corner and centre bosses embossed with a dome, star and foliate pattern; corner bosses with the text <quote>maria <unclear quantity="3" unit="chars"/>anis</quote>. <locus from="Spine" to="Spine" scheme="other"/>, in ink on a paper label: <quote>Missale Romanum N<hi rend="super">o</hi> 17</quote>; stamped in gold: <quote>A 176</quote>; in ink on a paper label glued on top of another paper label: <quote>e. 30. 6. 10.</quote>; in ink on the remnants of a paper label: <quote>18</quote>.</p>
                                <p>
                                    <dimensions type="binding">
                                        <height quantity="280" unit="mm"/>
                                        <width quantity="250" unit="mm"/>
                                        <depth quantity="95" unit="mm"/>
                                    </dimensions>
                                </p>
                                <decoNote type="tooling">
                                    <p>Blind-tooled pattern of single- and double-lined lozenges – on <locus from="RCO" to="RCO" scheme="other"/> with additional geometric shapes and flowers inside lozenges and at some of the intersecting lines.</p>
                                </decoNote>
                                <condition>Leather heavily worn. Endbands visible. Clasps and straps missing. <locus from="LCO" to="LCO" scheme="other"/>: lower right corner boss missing; <locus from="RCO" to="RCO" scheme="other"/>: upper left and lower right corner boss missing.</condition>
                            </binding>
                        </bindingDesc>
