                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="8r" to="106v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Proper of time</title>
                                <incipit defective="true">IN illo tempore Venit iohannes baptista (Matt. 3:1)</incipit>
                                <explicit>temporalis precepcio prefigurat Qui cum deo patre</explicit>
                                <note>
                                    <p>At least one leaf is missing before <locus from="8r" to="8r" scheme="folios"/>, resulting in loss of text; as it is, the proper of time begins in the middle of the First Sunday of Advent. The first part of the proper ends with the mass of Corpus Christi.</p>
                                    <p>One quire is missing after <locus from="91" to="91" scheme="folios"/>, which ends in the middle of the Gospel reading for Good Friday; <locus from="92r" to="92r" scheme="folios"/> begins with the end of the mass of Tuesday of Easter week.</p>
                                    <p>One quire is missing after <locus from="99" to="99" scheme="folios"/>, which ends with the reading for Friday of the third week of Eastertide; <locus from="100r" to="100r" scheme="folios"/> begins in the middle of the mass of Pentecost.</p>
                                    <p>Cross-references in Roman numerals to the pages for complete mass items are employed throughout the manuscript.</p>
                                </note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="106v" to="107v" scheme="folios"/>
