                                    <condition>Some stains and tears. Several leaves have been cut out; some of the stubs show traces of decorated initials, e.g <locus from="Stub_2r" to="Stub_2r" scheme="folios"/> (full-page), <locus from="Stub_5" to="Stub_5" scheme="folios"/>. Initials have also been cut out of <locus from="73" to="73" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="104" to="104" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="105" to="105" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="109" to="109" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="201" to="201" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="205" to="205" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="208" to="208" scheme="folios"/>. In some places, the blade has cut through the following leaf/leaves as well. Gaps in the contemporary foliation reveal that one full quire is missing between <locus from="91" to="92" scheme="folios"/> and one between <locus from="99" to="100" scheme="folios"/>. Catalogue notes dating to the 19th century describe the manuscript as comprising 259 leaves; however,
